					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Sounds like quite a task.  CHR-RAM games (battletoads and micromachines coming to mind) had a parralax effect where tiles that weren't in the foreground all shared a common tile (or was a 16x16 layout?) that was rewritten depending on the scroll of the foreground, but nothing on the scale of this.  You want to move that entire 'layer' at it's own scroll?
<br />
<br />I think setting CHR-RAM is just setting CHR-ROM quantity in the iNES header to zero.  then you just write in $0000-$1FFF to set your tiles.</div>

