						<div class="postbody">@tokumaru: Thank you for your wonderfully thorough response. You brought up some very important considerations. I may have to make some concessions here and there, but hearing everyone talk about how hard the effect is to pull off, I'm now <em>obligated</em> to do it. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />
<br />
<br />As for the randomness of the mountains, please disregard that. The image I posted is just a quick illustration of the concept. I'll definitely reduce the mountains to a repeating pattern of 32 pixels if not 16 pixels. Or if the mountains prove to be too troublesome, I may remove them entirely and just try to get a parallax skyline gradient.
<br />
<br />This particular level <em>only</em> scrolls vertically, so that should simplify things considerably.</div>

